const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-03-09 • Slayers</a>\n          <h1>Tarantula Slayer Money Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Tarantula Slayer remains one of the cleanest examples of repeatable slayer income because the method rewards speed and rhythm more than highlight-reel luck. That is the central lesson from current spider-slayer coverage. The best setups do not chase a fantasy jackpot every boss. They build a loop where spawn time, kill time and drop conversion stay tight enough that average value becomes reliable. In a game full of noisy coin claims, that kind of repeatability matters.</p>\n          <div class=\"note\"><strong>Primary source base:</strong> transcript grounding from lace's \"How to Master Tarantula Slayer\" coverage and broader slayer money discussions centered on consistency, route speed and realistic drop expectations.</div>\n          <h2>Spider slayer is a tempo method</h2>\n          <p>The attractive part of Tarantula Slayer is not just the drop table. It is the tempo. Faster spawn access, manageable routes and a clean combat loop mean more bosses completed in the same window, which smooths variance and lets drop averages actually show up. Players who evaluate Tarantula Slayer only through a single rare drop are missing why the method holds up. It is a consistency play first and a jackpot method second.</p>\n          <p>This is also what makes the boss easier to compare against other slayers. If one route gives weaker-looking peak drops but far better kill cadence, it may still win on practical income. That tradeoff is visible across recent creator discussions. The best slayer money is rarely the boss with the most dramatic screenshot. It is often the boss that allows the most clean repetitions with the least downtime and frustration.</p>\n          <h2>Gear matters, but route speed matters more than flex items</h2>\n          <p>Spider Slayer still needs a competent setup, but once the minimum combat threshold is crossed the next big improvement usually comes from execution quality rather than luxury spending. Better movement between spawns, faster boss resets and fewer sloppy fights do more for average income than buying random prestige pieces without a plan. That is an important correction because slayer discourse often gets distorted by players showing off gear before explaining the actual route logic.</p>\n          <p>Use the live tools to value the drop table and check whether the market is currently rewarding the route. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a> catches webs, TAP and book swings in real time, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">SkyCofl low supply</a> flags rare spider drops worth holding, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz</a> ranks the spider product family by 24h movement, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a> tells you whether the bazaar side will absorb your inventory at median price. Tarantula Slayer is strongest when you combine decent gear with a disciplined loop and current pricing, not when you blindly copy somebody else&apos;s loadout.</p>\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/slayer-money-making-guide-2026\">Best Slayer Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/magic-find-slayer-roi\">Magic Find ROI for Slayer Grinding</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\">Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div><h3>Best paired tools</h3><ul class=\"tool-list\"><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">SkyCofl low supply</a></li><li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz trends</a></li><li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/auction-flips\">BazaarPro auction flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li></ul></div>\n          <div><h3>Best for</h3><p>Players who want a slayer route based on repeatability instead of hoping one rare drop carries the whole session.</p></div>\n          <div><h3>Source videos</h3><p>lace's \"How to Master Tarantula Slayer\" is the clearest reference here because it frames the boss as a speed-and-consistency grind rather than a gambling machine.</p></div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
